      <bioghist>
        <head>Biographical/Historical Note</head>
        <p>In 1957 the City Council entered into a contract with the Virginia Department of Highways
          to widen Washington Street (Route 29-211) from East Fairfax Street to the north corporate
          limits. This was in lieu of making Maple Street a one-way road south and Washington Street
          one-way north. There was an additional project that continued the widening of Washington
          Street farther south to Cavalier Lane and Greenway Boulevard and later to Graham Road.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <!-- DACS 3.1 -->
      <scopecontent>
        <head>Scope and Content</head>
        <p>Most of the files contain correspondence with the property owners and with the State
          Department of Highways. These concern assessments of the property, rights-of-way, and
          property lists. There are also blueprints that list the property owners.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <!-- DACS 3.2 -->
      <arrangement>
        <head>Arrangement</head>
        <p>Most of the files are correspondence and are arranged chronologically.</p>
      </arrangement>
    </descgrp>
